I've been going to Odeon since...1986 (it opened in 1980) and it hasn't changed much, has it?  Any restaurant that has been open for 32 years must have some success factors, no?  If not, then restaurants would never close, right?  Go here and you'll see why they close.  From Fiona's smiling face when you walk in, to basic, standard food, that is just right.  Nothing flashy, but just spot-on as they say in one of my homelands!!  Plus where else do you get to rub shoulders with Geoffrey Rush, DeNiro and......
